  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">ACT Ubumbano Solidarity Hub</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Increased community agency, mobilisation organising and communities are empowered to claim and defending their rights and lead their own struggles (in an inclusive way).
 Joined-up impact that is not limited by thematic silos and connects grass-roots community actions and voice with national, regional and global policy advocacy across gender, economic and environmental justice.Collaborations forming to challenge social injustice and contribute to the transformation of structures of injustice and inequality.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This work is implemented by ACT Ubumbano and CLPs role is as local host organisation. 
ACT Ubumbano is a network of Southern African and European organisations working for economic, gender and environmental justice. This is done through facilitating critical reflection on our social justice practice, listening to the voices of those who are most affected by injustice, and supporting innovative and collaborative solidarity initiatives that address unjust power relations globally.
We intersect the three thematic pillars of i) Gender Justice &amp; SRHR, ii) Economic Justice and iii) Environmental/Climate Justice into these action areas:
&#x2022;	Promoting community voice and action
&#x2022;	 Learning from our practice (including local and thematic learning events and exchange visits)
&#x2022;	Protecting human rights including women&#x2019;s rights defenders
&#x2022;	Connecting people globally (south-south and north-south)
&#x2022;	Resourcing solidarity (in which we also jointly explore new southern and northern philanthropy options)</narrative>
  </description>
